definition: (bird species of China) golden eagle (Aquila chrysaetos)
gold/chemical element Au/generic term for lustrous and ductile metals/money/golden/highly respected/one of the eight categories of ancient musical instruments 八音[ba1 yin1]

sentences.english: Then, golden eagle came out, lonely chanted among my palm prints.
sentences.chinese: 然后，金雕出现，在我的掌纹间孤独歌吟。

sentences.english: This helicopter is used by the flight group “Berkuts” (golden eagles) that performs difficult flights on military helicopters.
sentences.chinese: “金雕”飞行队用这架直升机做高难度飞行表演。

sentences.english: Concealed by snowfall, the chase is watched by golden eagles circling above.
sentences.chinese: 受大雪所掩盖，大通是观看的上空盘旋，金雕。

sentences.english: I like golden eagles best of all the birds.
sentences.chinese: 所有鸟当中，我最喜欢金雕。

sentences.english: The belt only, adorned with studs and carvings of gold, he took and clasped round his own body.
sentences.chinese: 他仅仅取下装饰着金扣和金雕的腰带，系在自己身上。

sentences.english: High up on the sides of a Scottish cliff, golden eagles nest in an aerie.
sentences.chinese: 苏格兰高耸的悬崖边上有金雕的窝巢。

sentences.english: Finally, in order to protect her Wolf sun, end up with golden eagles.
sentences.chinese: 最后，她为了保护自己的狼孙，与金雕同归于尽了。
